---

<script is:inline>
  (function () {
    var t = localStorage.getItem('colorTheme') || 'cp';
    if (t !== 'cp' && /\/cp\/kanban\/?$/.test(location.pathname)) {
      location.replace('/components/kanban');
    }
  })();
</script>

<DocsLayout
  title="Kanban (Costpoint)"
  description="Costpoint Kanban application shell: board header, field cards, and kanbanView JSON mapping."
>
  <article class="space-y-12">
    <header class="page-header page-header--compact">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <h1 class="page-header__title page-header__title--sm">Kanban (Costpoint)</h1>
        <span class="badge badge--primary">CP Only</span>
      </div>
      <p class="page-header__description">
        The <strong>Costpoint</strong> Kanban matches the Deltek Costpoint board chrome (grey board band, board header, column accents) with configurable field cards. An optional dark application toolbar can be supplied via the <code class="text-primary">cp-toolbar</code> slot in the host app. Use with <code class="text-primary">html.theme-cp</code> and Costpoint tokens. The default task-board Kanban (title bar, rich cards, progress) is documented on the
        <a href="/components/kanban" class="text-primary underline">Kanban</a> page for other product themes.
      </p>
    </header>

    <nav class="article-nav">
      <a href="#examples" class="article-nav__link"><Icon name="eye" size="sm" /> Examples</a>
      <a href="#props" class="article-nav__link"><Icon name="queue-list" size="sm" /> Props</a>
      <a href="#json-config" class="article-nav__link"><Icon name="code-bracket" size="sm" /> JSON</a>
      <a href="#integration" class="article-nav__link"><Icon name="arrow-path" size="sm" /> Integration</a>
      <a href="#accessibility" class="article-nav__link"><Icon name="check-badge" size="sm" /> Accessibility</a>
    </nav>

    <section id="examples" class="space-y-8">
      <h2 class="section__title">Example</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl">
        Use <code>variant="costpoint"</code> with <code>cardFieldsConfig</code> and costpoint-shaped <code>columns</code>. The shell uses Costpoint chrome tokens (grey board band, teal active states on controls). Drag-and-drop, virtualization, save orchestration, and backend queries are implemented by the host application.
      </p>

      <ExampleSection
        title="Costpoint Kanban (MVP shell)"
        description="Board header (Showing/Sorted by, search), five columns with multiple field cards each (same primary/header style as the default Kanban board), teal Load more (n), and Costpoint field cards + Open record."
      >
        <div class="w-full overflow-x-auto min-h-[520px]">
          <Kanban
            variant="costpoint"
            cardFieldsConfig={cpCardFieldsConfig}
            columns={costpointColumns}
            cpRecordShown={13}
            cpRecordTotal={127}
            cpSortedBy="Due Date"
            cpScrollColumnIndex={4}
          />
        </div>
      </ExampleSection>
    </section>

    <section id="props">
      <h2 class="section__title">Props</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary mb-3">Kanban (costpoint variant)</h3>
          <PropsTable props={kanbanCostpointProps} />
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary mb-3">KanbanCardCostpoint</h3>
          <PropsTable props={kanbanCardCostpointProps} />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="json-config" class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="section__title">JSON configuration (kanbanView)</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary max-w-3xl">
        Types and an example payload live in <code>src/types/kanban-view-config.ts</code> (<code>KanbanViewConfig</code>, <code>EXAMPLE_KANBAN_VIEW_JSON</code>). Map JSON paths to UI as follows:
      </p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="min-w-full text-sm border border-light rounded-md">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-elevated text-left">
              <th class="p-3 border-b border-light">JSON path</th>
              <th class="p-3 border-b border-light">UI</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-primary">
            <tr><td class="p-3 border-b border-light font-mono text-xs">kanbanView.board.*</td><td class="p-3 border-b border-light">CSS variables: sizing (<code>--kanban-cp-min-column-width</code>, <code>--kanban-cp-card-height</code>, …), chrome (<code>--kanban-cp-chrome-toolbar-bg</code>, <code>--kanban-cp-chrome-board-bg</code>, …), and <code>--kanban-cp-card-surface</code>. Defaults are in <code>tokens.css</code> on <code>html.theme-cp</code>; CP dark mode remaps chrome, accents, and card surface to the CP semi-dark palette on <code>html.theme-cp.dark</code>.</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="p-3 border-b border-light font-mono text-xs">kanbanView.columns[n]</td><td class="p-3 border-b border-light">Column title, count; <code>headerColorLight</code> (hex) → column primary top-border accent</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="p-3 border-b border-light font-mono text-xs">kanbanView.cardFields.fields</td><td class="p-3 border-b border-light"><code>cardFieldsConfig</code> + per-record <code>valuesByFieldName</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="p-3 border-b border-light font-mono text-xs">kanbanView.colorRules</td><td class="p-3 border-b border-light">Resolved in the host; apply optional classes (e.g. <code>graphicalClass</code>) to cards</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted">Example JSON (abbreviated):</p>
      <pre class="p-4 bg-elevated rounded-md overflow-x-auto text-xs font-mono text-primary whitespace-pre-wrap">{EXAMPLE_KANBAN_VIEW_JSON}</pre>
    </section>

    <section id="integration" class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="section__title">Application integration</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-secondary max-w-3xl">
        <li><strong class="text-primary">In scope here:</strong> layout regions, CP-scoped CSS, field/spacer rules, styleId fallback classes, and TypeScript models aligned to MVP JSON.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-primary">Host application:</strong> drag-and-drop (hold-to-drag, silhouette, column drop targets), horizontal scroll sync with arrow navigation, virtualized columns/cards, client quick-search filtering after three characters on loaded data, 500-record cap messaging, save pipeline with board freeze and notifications, query/sort inheritance across Table/Form/Kanban, and persistence of Kanban JSON configuration.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-primary">React:</strong> import <code>Kanban</code> with <code>variant="costpoint"</code> and <code>KanbanCardCostpoint</code> if composing cards separately; ensure <code>html.theme-cp</code> (and tokens) are loaded — see <code>@dltkfrancesmunoz/harmony-react</code> package styles.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="accessibility" class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="section__title">Accessibility</h2>

      <div class="a11y-card">
        <h3 class="a11y-card__title">
          <Icon name="tag" size="sm" />
          Costpoint shell
        </h3>
        <p class="a11y-card__text">
          If you provide a custom <code>cp-toolbar</code>, disable record-level actions with <code>aria-disabled</code> where appropriate and use <code>aria-current</code> on the active view in the view switcher. Quick search is a labeled <code>type="search"</code> input. Cards expose field values via tooltips for truncated text; the Move control uses a listbox pattern from the Dropdown. Wire <strong>Open record</strong> and any custom toolbar navigation in the host application for full keyboard and screen reader flows.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="a11y-card">
        <h3 class="a11y-card__title">
          <Icon name="tag" size="sm" />
          Semantic structure
        </h3>
        <p class="a11y-card__text">
          The board uses semantic regions for the shell; columns use groups with descriptive labels. See the general <a href="/components/kanban#accessibility" class="text-primary underline">Kanban accessibility</a> section for column and card structure.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</DocsLayout>
